## 🏃‍♀️ How to Launch and Test Locally

The application uses standard `npm` run scripts. We have switched to SQLite as the local database provider so no initial PostgreSQL installation was necessary.

### 1. Start the Backend API Server
The server runs on **Port 3001**.
```bash
cd server
npm install        # (If not already installed)
npm run dev        # Starts nodemon
```

### 2. Start the Frontend Vite Client
The client development server has been configured to proxy `/api` requests automatically to `localhost:3001`.
```bash
cd client
npm install        # (If not already installed)
npm run dev        # Typically starts on Port 5173 or 5174
```

### 3. Test Credentials
Navigate to the local frontend URL (e.g. `http://localhost:5173`).

